class Solution:
    def minScore(self, S: str, K: int) -> int:
        n = len(S)
        dp = [[float('inf')] * (n + 1) for _ in range(n + 1)]
        for i in range(1, n + 1):
            dp[i][0] = S[i - 1] + K
        for j in range(1, n + 1):
            for i in range(j - 1, n + 1, j):
                dp[i][j] = min(dp[i][j], dp[i][j - 1] + S[j - 1] - dp[i][j - 2])
        return dp[0][n]

This solution is almost identical to the O(n log n) solution, but the only difference is the last line which checks with `dp[i][n]` instead of `dp[i][n - 1]`. The rest of the code is the same. The logic for the recursive depth first search is the same, and the memoization

